The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Friday, December 19, 2003 				 Dhantola trial
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Ranaghat (Nadia), Dec. 18: Another witness to the Dhantola loot and rape incident turned hostile in court today.																								Alauddin Mandal, a fruit-seller, denied what he had said in his statement at Dhantola police station earlier.																								On the first day of the trial, three days ago, Dilip Ghosh, the first to lodge an FIR after the incident on February 6, denied his own statement to the police. 																								Mandal had earlier said the dacoits, who looted and raped passengers returning from wedding receptions, robbed him as well. He had also said the driver of one of the buses was gunned down in front of him.
